description:
{ FOOD :: 4/5 stars }
*   Shredded Beef Pabellón, had a lot of flavor and was packed with meat.  unfortunately similar to the other reviews it was too "juicy".  by the time it arrived at the table, the bottom side of the arepas was so soaked that i couldn't pick it up w/o it falling apart
*   Nachos PICA PICA, tons of flavor.  the guasacaca sauce was YUMMY (tasted like a creama of some sort, just plain goodness).  con, had large slices of raw red onions and that fact isn't detailed on the menu.  if it had been, i would've requested sans onions

{ SERVICE :: 4/5 stars }
*   order taker, saw us looking at the menu and asked if it was our first time there and if we wanted her to explain the menu.  which we did... so she proceeded to provide us with the 411
*   food runner, was ok. she wasn't very friendly but she also wasn't rude

{ ATMOSPHERE :: 3.5 stars }
*   clean-ish, when the place gets busy, no one buses the tables.  so either you have to do it yourself and/or hope the previous person was kind enough to clean their mess (even if they tipped)
*   place is small, so it gets full fast
*   fairly cool (in temp) considering there is no AC, their ceiling fans work!
